 the &quot;New to FV?&quot; sticky topic.  Hopefully that will help!<br><br>LANGUAGE FAQ<br>--------------------------<br><br>1) &quot;How do I see what languages I can speak?&quot;<br><br>Three ways: Look at the bottom of your skill list, right-click on the text box (in the parchment screen mode, not F10 mode) and click on the language at the top of the screen to cycle through, or type /language help.<br><br>3) &quot;Hey, I know two languages!  How do I change what language I'm using?&quot;<br><br>If you use the text box method, the language you leave at the top of the box when you right-click out of it will be language you'll speak from then on.  You can also type /language #, where # is the number that shows up next to that language when you use /language help.<br><br>4) &quot;I want to speak a different language.  How do I learn a language I don't already know?&quot;<br><br>Two ways: train a point at your guild, or have someone speak it to you.  You'll know you've learned when you get a little message that says:<br><br>     Your language skill has improved.<br><br>You'll have to zone to see the new language show up on your list.  In fact, when learning a language, the game won’t recognize that you’ve gained anything in a language skill until you’ve zoned.<br><br>5) &quot;Hmm.  I don't want to waste my training points.  How do I learn a language from someone?&quot;<br><br>The only ways are to listen to them speak the language in /say, or /group with them and use /gsay.  I believe you have to be in relatively close proximity (/say range) in order to actually learn.<br><br>6) &quot;Keen!  So I can just sit there and have them spam me in /gsay to master Gnoll?”<br><br>Not quite.  There’s a timer on Firiona Vie that makes it so you can only learn one language point in ANY language each hour you are in a particular zone.  To reset that timer, you have to either wait the hour or zone.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  EDIT (Thanks Bjond!):</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Language skills have a per-level cap on Firiona Vie, just like your regular skills.  The formula is: (level + 1) X 5.  So in order to learn a language to Master, you will have to be 19th level or higher.<br><br>7) “How much in a language can someone else teach me?”<br><br>Someone can teach someone else up to one point higher than their own skill in the language.  Because of this, it’s common for two people to team up to master a particular language after one person trains a point in it.  This person will then teach their partner that one point, they’ll both zone, then teach each other one point higher.  Repeat until Mastery.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    “So that’s all there is about this language thing?”<br><br>Probably not, but that’s all I can think of right now.  If you have another question that I forgot, please ask so we can get the answer here for everyone!<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: Bump</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.alienexplorer.com/clipart/images5/wolf.pawprint2.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/2/02 8:38:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 1:57:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Doesn't go with the flow, but...</span><hr size=1> Just want to add a great and effective way for a group to teach a couple people a language. First, get by a zone. There has to be two people who know the language for this to work as effectively as it does. Park one person on the other side of the zone. Now, begin spamming. Soon as one of thegroup members goes up a point, they zone to the other side, where the other teacher will be spamming. By the time they've actually zoned and can move, they should have gone up a point already, if they've got a good Int and their zone times are slowed thanks to that damn Luclin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 4:40:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Another minor tidbit ..</span><hr size=1> .. is to use one character per line and 5 lines in your language lesson.  You get one chance per line in a new language to improve.  More characters per line just slows down the rate at which you can spam (and thus also the rate at which you learn).  Also, be sure to use /gsay and turn off group chat.  This will help ensure your improvement message is not scrolled off in a blizzard of spam and it won't annoy others that might be at the zone.  If you have a slow link, absolutely use 1 char per line or you can cause both yourself and your pupil to go linkdead.<br><br>You have to be level 19 or higher to master a language.  For an idea on how long it takes to master a language, multiply your zoning time by 100; eg. 30s zoning time means at least 50 minutes to master a language.  I've mastered all the racial (born) tongues and it varied from 35 minutes to 110 with 10-15s zone time, average about 45 minutes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umoandor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Moandor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 12:18:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Firiona Vie Language FAQ</span><hr size=1> Great thread Kimaya <br><br>ok....now I would like to know.... is anyone planning an upcoming language fair? <br><br>I really need to learn Human, and at least one other practical language of evil race (e.g. Ogre Troll or Dark Speech) <br><br>In return I will teach Teir'Dal, the language of love <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 3:48:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1104.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Firiona Vie Language FAQ</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;If you have a slow link, absolutely use 1 char per line or you can cause both yourself and your pupil to go linkdead.&gt;&gt;<br><br>That's not a problem if you use /serverfilter on and turn groupchat off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubarteby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barteby</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 